   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Traffic Accidents in New York City "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The goal of this project is to find out:\n",
    "- The time of day when most accidents occur\n",
    "- The dealiest time for motorists, cyclists and pedestrians\n",
    "- The major contributing factors to traffic accidents\n",
    "- The major car types in traffic accidents\n",
    "- A predictive model that estimates the likelihood of a fatal traffic accident"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data Preparation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This dataset is fetched from https://www.kaggle.com/pavetr/nypdcollisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(\"NYPD_Motor_Vehicle_Collisions.csv\", low_memory=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Change column names to title case."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.columns = map(str.title, df.columns)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Change all text variables to title case."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = df.applymap(lambda x: x.title() if type(x) == str else x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Drop irrelevant columns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.drop([\"Zip Code\", \"On Street Name\", \"Cross Street Name\", \"Off Street Name\", \"Unique Key\"], axis=1, inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Subset the dataset for a specific time frame."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   "source": [
    "date = pd.DataFrame(df[\"Date\"].str.split(\"/\").tolist(), columns=\"Month Day Year\".split())\n",
    "pd.options.display.max_rows = 100\n",
    "print(date.groupby([\"Year\", \"Month\"]).size())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data document the traffic accidents from July 2012 to August 2017."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will subset subset the data to only include observations between January 2013 and December 2016."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "date = pd.DataFrame(df[\"Date\"].str.split(\"/\").tolist(), columns=\"Month Day Year\".split())\n",
    "df.drop([\"Date\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df = date.join(df, how=\"inner\")\n",
    "df = df[df.Year != \"2012\"]\n",
    "df = df[df.Year != \"2017\"]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Create a **Weekday** column."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"Date\"] = df[\"Year\"] + \"-\" + df[\"Month\"] + \"-\" + df[\"Day\"]\n",
    "df.drop([\"Month\", \"Day\", \"Year\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df[\"Time\"] = df[\"Time\"] + \":00\"\n",
    "df[\"DATETIME\"] = df[\"Date\"] + \" \" + df[\"Time\"]\n",
    "df[\"DateTime\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"DATETIME\"])\n",
    "df.drop([\"Time\", \"Date\", \"DATETIME\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df[\"Weekday\"] = df[\"DateTime\"].dt.day_name()\n",
    "df[\"Time\"] = df[\"DateTime\"].dt.time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6. Impute missing locations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "New York city is made up of five boroughs â€“ Brooklyn, Queens, Manhattan, The Bronx and Staten Island. Our data might contain observations in nearby New Jersey or other parts of New York State. We will drop those observations. Since we do not want any traffic accident from other counties / states outside New York City to bias our study, we will drop all observations with missing locations (missing latitude / longitude, location coordinates and borough). However, this doesn't come without cost as we might also drop traffic accidents happened in New York City."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "queens = df[df.Borough == \"Queens\"]\n",
    "brooklyn = df[df.Borough == \"Brooklyn\"]\n",
    "bronx = df[df.Borough == \"Bronx\"]\n",
    "manhattan = df[df.Borough == \"Manhattan\"]\n",
    "staten = df[df.Borough == \"Staten Island\"]\n",
    "df = df[~df.Borough.isin([\"Queens\", \"Brooklyn\", \"Bronx\", \"Manhattan\", \"Staten Island\"])]\n",
    "df[\"Location Missing\"] = df[[\"Borough\", \"Latitude\", \"Longitude\", \"Location\"]].isna().all(axis=1)\n",
    "df = df[df[\"Location Missing\"] == False]\n",
    "assert df.Latitude.isna().sum() == 0\n",
    "assert df.Longitude.isna().sum() == 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For observations with missing borough but existing latitude and longitude, we will use reversed geocoding to find out the traffic accidents that actually happened in New York City."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Loading formatted geocoded file...\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import reverse_geocoder as rg\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"Coordinate\"] = list(zip(df.Latitude, df.Longitude))\n",
    "geo = rg.search(list(df.Coordinate))\n",
    "admin1 = []\n",
    "admin2 = []\n",
    "names = []\n",
    "for i in geo:\n",
    "    names.append((list(i.items())[2])[1])\n",
    "    admin1.append((list(i.items())[3])[1])\n",
    "    admin2.append((list(i.items())[4])[1])\n",
    "df[\"name\"] = names\n",
    "df[\"admin1\"] = admin1\n",
    "df[\"admin2\"] = admin2\n",
    "df.loc[df.name == \"Manhattan\", \"Borough\"] = \"Manhattan\"\n",
    "df.loc[df.admin2 == \"Bronx\", \"Borough\"] = \"Bronx\"\n",
    "df = df[df[\"admin1\"] == \"New York\"] # Drop New Jersey\n",
    "df.loc[df.name == \"Borough of Queens\", \"Borough\"] = \"Queens\"\n",
    "df.loc[df.name == \"Brooklyn\", \"Borough\"] = \"Brooklyn\"\n",
    "df.loc[df.name == \"Staten Island\", \"Borough\"] = \"Staten Island\"\n",
    "df = df[~df[\"Borough\"].isnull()]\n",
    "df = pd.concat([df, queens, manhattan, staten, brooklyn, bronx], sort=True)\n",
    "df.drop([\"name\", \"admin1\", \"admin2\", \"Coordinate\", \"Longitude\", \"Latitude\", \"Location\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "assert df.Borough.isna().sum() == 0 # There should be no missing boroughs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(649585, 23)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,

   ],
   "source": [
    "df.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7. Generate dummy variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "contributing_factor = [\"Contributing Factor Vehicle 1\", \n",
    "                       \"Contributing Factor Vehicle 2\", \n",
    "                       \"Contributing Factor Vehicle 3\",\n",
    "                       \"Contributing Factor Vehicle 4\",\n",
    "                       \"Contributing Factor Vehicle 5\"]\n",
    "vehicle_type = [\"Vehicle Type Code 1\",\n",
    "                \"Vehicle Type Code 2\",\n",
    "                \"Vehicle Type Code 3\",\n",
    "                \"Vehicle Type Code 4\",\n",
    "                \"Vehicle Type Code 5\"]\n",
    "df[\"Contributing Factor\"] = df[contributing_factor].values.tolist()\n",
    "df.drop(contributing_factor, axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df[\"Vehicle Type\"] = df[vehicle_type].values.tolist()\n",
    "df.drop(vehicle_type, axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "contributing_factor = df[\"Contributing Factor\"].values.tolist()\n",
    "contributing_factor = [list(set(i)) for i in contributing_factor]\n",
    "df.drop([\"Contributing Factor\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df[\"Contributing Factor\"] = contributing_factor\n",
    "vehicle_type = df[\"Vehicle Type\"].values.tolist()\n",
    "vehicle_type = [list(set(i)) for i in vehicle_type]\n",
    "df.drop([\"Vehicle Type\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df[\"Vehicle Type\"] = vehicle_type\n",
    "# Reference: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29034928/pandas-convert-a-column-of-list-to-dummies\n",
    "contributing_factor = df[\"Contributing Factor\"].apply(pd.Series).stack().str.get_dummies().sum(level=0).add_prefix(\"Contributing Factor: \")\n",
    "vehicle_type = df[\"Vehicle Type\"].apply(pd.Series).stack().str.get_dummies().sum(level=0).add_prefix(\"Vehicle Type: \")\n",
    "df.drop([\"Contributing Factor\", \"Vehicle Type\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "df = pd.merge(df, contributing_factor, left_index=True, right_index=True, how=\"left\")\n",
    "df = pd.merge(df, vehicle_type, left_index=True, right_index=True, how=\"left\")\n",
    "vehicle_type_col = [i for i in list(df.columns) if i.startswith(\"Vehicle Type: \")]\n",
    "df[vehicle_type_col] = df[vehicle_type_col].fillna(0)\n",
    "df[vehicle_type_col] = df[vehicle_type_col].astype(int)\n",
    "contributing_factor_col = [i for i in list(df.columns) if i.startswith(\"Contributing Factor: \")]\n",
    "df[contributing_factor_col] = df[contributing_factor_col].fillna(0)\n",
    "df[contributing_factor_col] = df[contributing_factor_col].astype(int)\n",
    "df.drop([\"Location Missing\", \"Time\"], axis=1, inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "assert df.isnull().sum().max() == 0"
   ]
  },

    "By now, the dateset is clean and tidy."
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"Hour\"] = df[\"DateTime\"].dt.hour\n",
    "vis1_df = df.groupby([\"Weekday\", \"Hour\"]).agg([\"count\"]).iloc[:,0].reset_index()\n",
    "vis1_df.columns = vis1_df.columns.droplevel()\n",
    "vis1_df.columns = [\"Weekday\", \"Hour\", \"Count\"]\n",
    "labels = []\n",
    "for i in range(24):\n",
    "    if i < 10:\n",
    "        if i==9:\n",
    "            label = \"0\" + str(i) + \":00-\" + str(i+1) + \":00\"\n",
    "            labels.append(label)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            label = \"0\" + str(i) + \":00-0\" + str(i+1) + \":00\"\n",
    "            labels.append(label)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        if i == 23:\n",
    "            label = str(i) + \":00-00:00\"\n",
    "            labels.append(label)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            label = str(i) + \":00-\" + str(i+1) + \":00\"\n",
    "            labels.append(label)\n",
    "hour = list(range(24))\n",
    "hour_label_dict = dict(zip(hour, labels))\n",
    "vis1_df[\"Time of Day\"] = vis1_df[\"Hour\"].map(hour_label_dict)\n",
    "categories=[\"Monday\", \"Tuesday\", \"Wednesday\", \"Thursday\", \"Friday\", \"Saturday\", \"Sunday\"]\n",
    "vis1_df[\"Weekday\"] = pd.Categorical(vis1_df[\"Weekday\"], categories=categories, ordered=True)\n",
    "vis1_df = vis1_df.sort_values(by=[\"Weekday\", \"Time of Day\"])\n",
    "data = vis1_df.pivot(index = \"Time of Day\", columns = \"Weekday\", values=\"Count\")\n",
    "plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(data, cmap=sns.color_palette(\"RdYlGn_r\", 10), annot=True, vmin=0, vmax=vis1_df.Count.max(), fmt=\"d\").set_title(\"What Time of Day Do Most Accidents Occur?\")\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"Fig1.png\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What is the deadliest time of day?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plotInjuriesDeaths(df, stratified):\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    df: dataframe\n",
    "    stratified: a boolean value indicating whether to stratify analysis by people's roles on the road.\n",
    "    This function plots injuries / deaths per 1000 accidents.\n",
    "    This function doesn't return any values.\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    if not stratified:\n",
    "        cols_to_keep = [\"DateTime\", \n",
    "                        \"Weekday\", \n",
    "                        \"Number Of Persons Injured\", \n",
    "                        \"Number Of Persons Killed\"]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        cols_to_keep = [\"Weekday\",\n",
    "                        \"DateTime\", \n",
    "                        \"Number Of Cyclist Injured\", \n",
    "                        \"Number Of Cyclist Killed\",\n",
    "                        \"Number Of Motorist Injured\",\n",
    "                        \"Number Of Motorist Killed\",\n",
    "                        \"Number Of Pedestrians Injured\", \n",
    "                        \"Number Of Pedestrians Killed\"]\n",
    "    temp_df = df[cols_to_keep]\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Hour\"] = df[\"DateTime\"].dt.hour\n",
    "    temp_df = temp_df.groupby([\"Weekday\", \"Hour\"]).agg([\"sum\", \"count\"]).reset_index()\n",
    "    temp_df.columns = temp_df.columns.droplevel()\n",
    "    if not stratified:\n",
    "        temp_df.columns = [\"Weekday\", \"Hour\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Persons Injured\", \n",
    "                           \"to_be_dropped\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Persons Killed\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df.drop([\"to_be_dropped\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Deaths per Thousand Accidents\"] = 1000 * temp_df[\"Number of Persons Killed\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Injuries per Thousand Accidents\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Persons Injured\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Hour\", \n",
    "                           \"Deaths per Thousand Accidents\", \n",
    "                           \"Injuries per Thousand Accidents\"]]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        temp_df.columns = [\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Hour\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Cyclist Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Accidents\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Cyclist Killed\", \n",
    "                           \"drop1\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Motorist Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"drop2\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Motorist Killed\",\n",
    "                           \"drop3\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Pedestrians Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"drop4\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Pedestrians Killed\",\n",
    "                           \"drop5\"]\n",
    "        temp_df.drop([\"drop1\",\"drop2\",\"drop3\",\"drop4\",\"drop5\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "        temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Hour\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Accidents\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Cyclist Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Cyclist Killed\", \n",
    "                           \"Number of Motorist Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Motorist Killed\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Pedestrians Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Number of Pedestrians Killed\"]]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Cyclists Injured\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Cyclist Injured\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Cyclists Killed\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Cyclist Killed\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Motorists Injured\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Motorist Injured\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Motorists Killed\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Motorist Killed\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Pedestrians Injured\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Pedestrians Injured\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df[\"Pedestrians Killed\"] = 1000* temp_df[\"Number of Pedestrians Killed\"] / temp_df[\"Number of Accidents\"]\n",
    "        temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Hour\", \n",
    "                           \"Cyclists Injured\", \n",
    "                           \"Cyclists Killed\", \n",
    "                           \"Motorists Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Motorists Killed\",\n",
    "                           \"Pedestrians Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Pedestrians Killed\"]]\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Time of Day\"] = temp_df[\"Hour\"].map(hour_label_dict)\n",
    "    temp_df.drop([\"Hour\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Weekday\"] = pd.Categorical(temp_df[\"Weekday\"], categories=categories, ordered=True)\n",
    "    if not stratified:\n",
    "        temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Time of Day\", \n",
    "                           \"Injuries per Thousand Accidents\", \n",
    "                           \"Deaths per Thousand Accidents\"]]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \n",
    "                           \"Time of Day\", \n",
    "                           \"Cyclists Injured\", \n",
    "                           \"Cyclists Killed\", \n",
    "                           \"Motorists Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Motorists Killed\",\n",
    "                           \"Pedestrians Injured\",\n",
    "                           \"Pedestrians Killed\"]]\n",
    "    temp_df = temp_df.sort_values(by=[\"Weekday\", \"Time of Day\"])\n",
    "    if not stratified:\n",
    "        injuries = temp_df.pivot(index = \"Time of Day\", columns = \"Weekday\", values=\"Injuries per Thousand Accidents\")\n",
    "        deaths = temp_df.pivot(index = \"Time of Day\", columns = \"Weekday\", values=\"Deaths per Thousand Accidents\")\n",

    "## At each hour, what is the major contributing factor to traffic accidents?"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",

    "def getMajorFactor(df, factor_prefix):\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    df: dataframe\n",
    "    factor_prefix: a string that can have values of either \"Contributing Factor\" or \"Vehicle Type\"\n",
    "    This function lists the major contributing factor / car type in each hour on each weekday. \n",
    "    This function doesn't return any values.\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    factors = [i for i in list(df.columns) if i.startswith(factor_prefix + \": \")]\n",
    "    temp_df = df[[\"Weekday\", \"DateTime\"] + factors]\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Hour\"] = temp_df[\"DateTime\"].dt.hour\n",
    "    temp_df = temp_df.groupby([\"Weekday\", \"Hour\"]).agg([\"sum\"]).reset_index()\n",
    "    temp_df.columns = temp_df.columns.droplevel()\n",
    "    temp_df.columns = [\"Weekday\", \"Hour\"] + factors\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Time of Day\"] = temp_df[\"Hour\"].map(hour_label_dict)\n",
    "    temp_df.drop([\"Hour\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "    temp_df = temp_df[[\"Weekday\", \"Time of Day\"] + factors]\n",
    "    temp_df[\"Weekday\"] = pd.Categorical(temp_df[\"Weekday\"], categories=categories, ordered=True)\n",
    "    temp_df = temp_df.sort_values(by=[\"Weekday\", \"Time of Day\"])\n",
    "    if factor_prefix == \"Contributing Factor\":\n",
    "        temp_df.drop([\"Contributing Factor: Unspecified\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "        factors.remove(\"Contributing Factor: Unspecified\")\n",
    "    temp_df[factor_prefix] = temp_df[factors].idxmax(axis=1)\n",
    "    temp_df.drop(factors, axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "    temp_df[factor_prefix] = temp_df[factor_prefix].str.replace(factor_prefix + \": \", \"\")\n",
    "    print(temp_df[factor_prefix].value_counts())"
   ]
  },

    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "# Drop irrelevant columns.\n",
    "md_df = df.drop([\"Number Of Cyclist Injured\", \n",
    "                 \"Number Of Cyclist Killed\", \n",
    "                 \"Number Of Motorist Injured\", \n",
    "                 \"Number Of Motorist Killed\",\n",
    "                 \"Number Of Pedestrians Injured\", \n",
    "                 \"Number Of Pedestrians Killed\", \n",
    "                 \"Number Of Persons Injured\"], axis=1)\n",
    "md_df[\"Hour\"] = md_df[\"DateTime\"].dt.hour\n",
    "md_df[\"Time of Day\"] = md_df[\"Hour\"].map(hour_label_dict)\n",
    "# Drop irrelevant columns.\n",
    "md_df.drop([\"Hour\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "md_df = pd.get_dummies(md_df, columns=[\"Borough\", \"Weekday\", \"Time of Day\"])\n",
    "# Create a binary variable indicating whether an accident is fatal\n",
    "md_df.loc[md_df[\"Number Of Persons Killed\"] > 0, \"Fatal Accident\"] = 1\n",
    "md_df[\"Fatal Accident\"] = md_df[\"Fatal Accident\"].fillna(0)\n",
    "# Drop irrelevant columns.\n",
    "md_df.drop([\"Number Of Persons Killed\", \"DateTime\"], axis=1, inplace=True)\n",
    "# All variables are binary.\n",
    "md_df = md_df.astype(\"int32\")\n",
    "y = md_df[\"Fatal Accident\"].values\n",
    "X = md_df.drop([\"Fatal Accident\"], axis=1).values\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = 0.3, random_state=25)"
   ]
